{
  "doc_id": "7764",
  "text": "The association between CAD and RCVS has been postulated in multiple case reports and has been confirmed in a prospective cohort study of 20 patients with both conditions, representing 12% of consecutive RCVS patients and 7% of consecutive CAD patients. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] The clinical presentation of RCVS plus CAD did not differ from that of isolated RCVS. However, in addition to the usual clinical presentation, associated neck pain was present in 75% of cases. [CITATION_4] The underlying mechanisms remain unclear. Further, the sequence of pathologies is unknown, that is, whether RCVS induces CAD, or vice versa. [CITATION_5] In our patient, RCVS has been identified prior to the VA dissection. Eventually a shared genetic predisposition for RCVS and CAD, potentially linked to migraine, is possible that remains to be confirmed, for example, in genetic studies. [CITATION_6] ",
